<section id="GUID-09885F9B-8303-55B8-B8D4-ADFDB2912D2A"><title>Introduction</title> <p>Extended
Light API is similar to the Light API but it supports more target devices.
It can be used with or without a notification. When the notification is required,
a callback pointer is implemented in the instance of the <xref href="GUID-BC043845-8907-340F-AD25-612DD5C08225.dita"><apiname>CHWRMExtendedLight</apiname></xref>.
The callback pointer is provided by the <xref href="GUID-BC043845-8907-340F-AD25-612DD5C08225.dita"><apiname>MHWRMExtendedLightObserver</apiname></xref> class. </p><p>Using
Extended Light API, you can perform any of the tasks listed in the procedure
section:</p></section>
